      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is a function using regular expressions to identify and extract mandatory requirements based on your specific text logic:\n\n```python\nimport re\n\ndef extract_requirements(text: str) -> list[str]:\n    # Pattern matches sentences with \"must\", \"requires\", \"mandatory\", \"obliged\"\n    regex = r\"(?:must|requires|is mandatory|is obliged)\\s+(.*)?(\\.\\s*$|\\,)\"\n    matches = re.findall(regex, text, flags=re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL)\n    return [match.strip() for match in matches if match.strip()]\n\ntest_parser()\n```\nThis script searches for the key phrases you identified and strips punctuation to match your expected output format exactly. You can also test this directly by running `extract_requirements(\"The data controller must implement appropriate technical measures to ensure security.\")`.",
